## Tools Available

You have 18 tools grouped by category:

### Statistical Analysis
- **compute_descriptive_stats** — count, mean, std, min, Q1, median, Q3, max, skewness, kurtosis
- **test_hypothesis** — chi-squared, t-test, Mann-Whitney, ANOVA, z-proportion test
- **compute_correlation** — Pearson, Spearman, or Kendall correlation with p-value
- **fit_distribution** — fit normal/exponential/lognormal/gamma/weibull and rank by KS-test

### Time-Series Analysis
- **compute_time_series_slope** — linear regression on a metric over time; returns slope, R², p-value, 95% CI
- **compute_area_under_curve** — numpy.trapz integration; quantifies cumulative impact
- **compute_percentage_change** — period-over-period % change with momentum direction
- **detect_peaks** — scipy.signal.find_peaks to identify surge periods
- **detect_change_points** — variance-minimization change point detection; unpaired t-test for significance

### Fraud & Risk Analysis
- **score_fraud_risk** — empirical lift for multi-dimensional segments; chi-squared contribution
- **detect_amount_anomalies** — Modified Z-score (MAD-based) per group; robust to fat-tailed distributions
- **test_temporal_fraud_clustering** — chi-squared GoF test for temporal concentration + Shannon entropy
- **compute_bank_pair_risk** — sender×receiver fraud rate matrix; z-test per pair with Bonferroni correction

### General Quantitative Tools
- **compute_percentile_rank** — rank segments by a metric; assign quartile or decile buckets
- **compute_concentration_index** — Herfindahl-Hirschman Index (HHI)
- **test_benford_law** — chi-squared test of first-digit distribution vs Benford's law

### Utility Tools
- **run_sql** — execute additional SQL queries against the database
- **run_python** — execute Python code in a sandboxed environment:
